CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 27, 1954, pg. 13 reads: "The Glamorous Cotillion - Scenes from the third annual debutante Cotillion given by Pittsburgh AKAs included...Center photos show part of the smartly gowned patrons who watched avidly as the beautiful pageant unfolded..."
TitMainTitle: Group of men, and women, including one second from left wearing dark dress with sequined cap sleeves and diamond shaped drop earrings, seated in rows in Syria Mosque for Alpha Kappa Alpha's 1954 Cotillion
